        "OBAT Helpers demonstrates a robust commitment to organizational health, as reflected in its <cite id=\"13\">100/100 scores for Culture and Leadership</cite> from Charity Navigator. Their governance is supported by a <cite id=\"14\">board of 22 members</cite> with <cite id=\"15\">100% independence</cite>, ensuring strong oversight. Furthermore, their direct service delivery model achieves a <cite id=\"16\">cost per beneficiary of approximately $163.70</cite>, which is considered efficient for integrated education and health services."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 2004, OBAT Helpers Inc. is a specialized humanitarian organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">empowering displaced and refugee communities</cite> in Bangladesh. The organization operates with a high degree of transparency, evidenced by its <cite id=\"2\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite> and an <cite id=\"3\">overall score of 90.90.33333333333333/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. OBAT's mission focuses on breaking the cycle of poverty through a multi-sectoral approach that includes <cite id=\"4\">education, healthcare, and W.A.S.H. initiatives</cite>. Financially, the organization reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $2,184,558</cite> in 2023, maintaining a lean operation with <cite id=\"6\">fundraising efficiency of $0.08 per $1 raised</cite>. This efficiency ensures that a significant portion of donor contributions directly supports their <cite id=\"7\">50 educational and training projects</cite> and <cite id=\"8\">3 health clinics</cite> serving camp residents and Rohingya refugees. As a <cite id=\"9\">zakat-eligible entity</cite>, OBAT provides a critical channel for Muslim donors to support the <cite id=\"10\">fuqara (poor) and masakin (needy)</cite> within marginalized displaced populations.",
